WorkItem.Description:
In Section 1.4, an example uses the constructor shorthand for populating an objects fields:

```TypeScript
class CPoint {
    constructor (public x: number, public y: number) { }
} 
```

This shorthand is not introduced until much later in the document.  Problematically, one cannot understand this example (and is quite confused by it!) if one does not know that this constructor syntax will set the object's x and y field to numbers.
